# Cosmic Ocean: Project Data Schema (V1)

*This document serves as the single source of truth for all portfolio content, metadata, and analytics interactions in Cosmic Ocean. It guarantees that the 3D application logic is fully decoupled from the portfolio content, allowing future updates without modifying application code.*

---

## 1. Core Architecture Strategy

### Single Source Of Truth
All text, images, coordinates, and skills live inside a single `content.json` file. The TypeScript application contains zero hardcoded strings regarding the developer's experience.

### Content Loading Strategy
**Data Source:** `public/data/content.json`
**Loading Phase:** The application fetches this JSON during the `Promise.all()` initialization step defined in the Technical Architecture Document. 
**State Hydration:** The JSON is validated against the schemas below and injected into a global `ContentManager` class via constructor injection. The UI and 3D world dynamically generate DOM elements and interaction triggers based entirely on this state.

---

## 2. Versioning & Validation Strategy

*   **Schema Versioning:** The root JSON object must contain a `buildInfo` object detailing the version.
*   **Forward Compatibility:** All new fields added in future years (2027+) must be defined as `optional` (`?`) in the TypeScript interface.
*   **Validation:** The schema is strictly validated on load. Any parsing failures populate the `validationErrors` array and disable the 3D scene, showing the error UI instead.

---

## 3. TypeScript Interfaces & JSON Schema

### 3.1 Root Schema
```typescript
interface PortfolioData {
    buildInfo: {
        version: string; // e.g., "1.0.0"
        buildDate: string; // ISO 8601
        commitHash: string; // e.g., "7f8a9c2"
    };
    featureFlags: {
        enableWhale: boolean;
        enableAudio: boolean;
        enableAnalytics: boolean;
        enableObservatory: boolean;
        enablePostProcessing: boolean;
    };
    assetManifest: {
        modelPath: string; // Base URL for GLB models
        audioPath: string; // Base URL for sound files
        texturePath: string; // Base URL for matcaps
        preloadPriority: string[]; // Array of essential asset filenames
    };
    developer: DeveloperSchema;
    resume: ResumeSchema;
    skills: SkillCategory[];
    projects: ProjectSchema[];
    observatoryTimeline: TimelineEvent[];
    worldTriggers: WorldTriggerSchema[];
    validationErrors?: string[]; // Populated internally for debugging bad JSON.
}
```

### 3.2 Developer / Resume Schema
```typescript
interface DeveloperSchema {
    name: string; // Required
    role: string; // Required (e.g., "Creative Frontend Engineer")
    email: string; // Required
    github: string; // Required
    linkedin: string; // Required
    tagline?: string; // Optional
}

interface ResumeSchema {
    summary: string[]; // Required. Array of paragraphs.
    experience: JobExperience[]; // Required
}

interface JobExperience {
    id: string; // Required. Unique identifier.
    company: string; // Required
    role: string; // Required
    startDate: string; // Required (e.g., "2024-01")
    endDate: string | "Present"; // Required
    bullets: string[]; // Required
}
```

### 3.3 Skills Schema
```typescript
interface SkillCategory {
    categoryName: string; // Required (e.g., "Languages", "3D Web")
    skills: Skill[]; // Required
}

interface Skill {
    id: string; // Required. Unique identifier.
    name: string; // Required (e.g., "TypeScript")
    iconUrl?: string; // Optional path to SVG
    level?: "Beginner" | "Intermediate" | "Advanced"; // Optional clarity for recruiters.
}
```

### 3.4 Project Schema (The Monoliths)
*Validation Rule: Every project must have a matching `worldTrigger` defined to spawn its monolith.*
```typescript
interface ProjectSchema {
    id: string; // Required. (e.g., "project-alpha")
    title: string; // Required
    year: number; // Required
    displayOrder: number; // Required. Controls UI list sorting.
    thumbnailUrl: string; // Required. Relative path to /public/assets/images/
    videoUrl?: string; // Optional fallback.
    techStackIds: string[]; // Required. Must map to Skill.id
    description: {
        problem: string; // Required
        solution: string; // Required
    };
    links: {
        liveDemo?: string; // Optional
        githubRepo?: string; // Optional
        caseStudy?: string; // Optional external link
    };
}
```

### 3.5 Observatory Timeline Schema
```typescript
interface TimelineEvent {
    year: number; // Required. Used for sorting.
    title: string; // Required
    description: string; // Required
    isMajorMilestone: boolean; // Required. If true, renders larger in UI.
}
```

### 3.6 World Trigger Schema
*Decouples 3D spatial layout from content. Adding a new project in 2028 simply means adding a new object here.*
```typescript
interface WorldTriggerSchema {
    id: string; // Required. Maps to Project.id or special landmarks ("harbor", "observatory").
    type: "project" | "harbor" | "observatory" | "reef"; // Required
    coordinates: {
        x: number; // Required
        z: number; // Required
    };
    triggerRadius: number; // Required
}
```

